Person class does not include NRIC field.

NRIC can be used to easier identify and search for the required person.

Let's add the NRIC field (specific for Singaporean format).

The program is based on managing patients and doctors as distinct
individuals.

Let's add Patient and Doctor classes to have a way to distinguish
between the two.

Person's role is not stored when closing the app.
Let's add a Role field to be able to store and keep track of people
when the app reopens.

commitResults.messageTitle: FindCommand: Update to find by NRIC
commitResults.messageBody:
The find command uses names, which may lead to mistakes.

Let's update the find command to search by NRIC to provide more
accurate results.

UniqueAppointmentList accounts for all hospital appointments to be
distinct in booking timings. But duplicate booking timings are only not
allowed within each patient, and allowed among different patients.

HospitalAppointmentList will only restrict duplicate bookings for each
patient.

Let's implement HospitalAppointmentList and remove
UniqueAppointmentList.

Appointment list shown in detailed person panel displays both dr's and
patient's nric. Poor UX as it is confusing as to which to refer to.

Patient's appointment list should only display the nric of the dr that
he is scheduled with. Doctor's appointment list should only display the
nric of the patient that he is scheduled with.

Let's improve the UX for appointment list.

commitResults.messageTitle: DeleteCommand class deletes by name in the list
commitResults.messageBody:
While name works fine, it is not secure and does not handle the case of having common shared names. If the list contains "John" and "John Doe" then delete n/John will delete "John". However the user might want to delete "John Doe" but accidentally pressed enter before typing out the rest of the name and the wrong "John" will be deleted.

Let's change the delete command to delete by NRIC. Since each person has a unique NRIC, there is no need to check for multiple person. The GUI will automatically delete the person with the respective NRIC.

The user no longer has to search for the person's index or name.
